The Edo State government has confirmed that one new case of coronavirus has been recorded in the state. The confirmation was made by the state Governor, Godwin Obaseki in a tweet via his Twitter account on Thursday. The tweet reads “ COVID-19 update as at 10:00 am, 14th May, 2020. “Edo recorded one new case of coronavirus disease. “Total number of confirmed cases – 89. “Total number of Active cases – 72. “13 patients have been discharged with 4 deaths recorded. “Residents are advised to stay home, stay safe and observe social distancing.”